snippet.title: Best VGM 1239 - Pop'n Music 8 - Marigold
snippet.description:
See also:
Best VGM 1062 - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zxZROhq4Lz0

A collection of my favorite videogame music. Note that most of them are from games I played so I might miss some great ones from games I never played.

Arcade / PS2
Pop'n Music 8 (2002)
Marigold
SHORTCUTS

Lyrics brought to you by SD:

Papapa, papapa....

Encountered before
A fat baby has no mouth
Necessary goal
It's a speaking girl from south
What do you feel?
Everything turning around me
Where do you come from?
I come from you

Looking, looking, talking, talking
Something uniting me to call.
Passing, passing, living, living
Nothing defending me from all.
Stuffing, stuffing, sleeping, sleeping
Something releasing me in the porch.
Picking, picking, finding, finding 
Nothing smoking me with match

Please show its smoke like sweet marshmallow smell

Can you count, marigold?
Can you count their forms?
Counting 3, Counting 4...
